ng, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":47,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Roger Del’outhe was born in 1408, in Parkhall, Warwickshire, England as the son of Sibell De Belgrave. He had at least 1 daughter with Thomasine De Arden. He died in 1461, in Cambridge, Gloucestershire, England, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1408–1461":"1408–1461","1412–1430":"1412–1430","1430–1448":"1430–1448","1400–1421":"1400–1421","1448":"1448","August 1421":"august 1421","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1421":"1421","1430":"1430","1461":"1461","1408":"1408","after 1430":"pärast 1430","Cambridge, Gloucestershire, England":"Cambridge, Gloucestershire, England","Durham, Durham, England":"Durham, Durham, England","London, England":"London, England","Parkhall, Warwickshire, England":"Parkhall, Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"1408–1461":"1408–1461","1412–1430":"1412–1430","1430–1448":"1430–1448","1400–1421":"1400–1421","1448":"1448","August 1421":"elokuu 1421","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1421":"1421","1430":"1430","1461":"1461","1408":"1408","after 1430":"1430 jälkeen","Cambridge, Gloucestershire, England":"Cambridge, Gloucestershire, England","Durham, Durham, England":"Durham, Durham, England","London, England":"London, England","Parkhall, Warwickshire, England":"Par